21A.120 | American Dream: Exploring Class in the US | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=21A.120 American Dream: Exploring Class in the US | instructors:C. Walley  description:Americans have historically preferred to think of the United States in classless terms, as a land of economic opportunity equally open to all. Yet, social class remains a central fault line in the US. Subject explores the experiences and understandings of class among Americans positioned at different points along the US social spectrum. Considers a variety of classic frameworks for analyzing social class and uses memoirs, novels and ethnographies to gain a sense of how class is experienced in daily life and how it intersects with other forms of social difference such as race and gender. 
