21A.819 | Qualitative Research Methods | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=21A.819 Qualitative Research Methods | instructors:G. Jones  textbook:Tricks of the Trade: How to Think about Your Research While You're Doing It (Becker, Howard S.) description:Training in the design and practice of qualitative research. Organized around illustrative texts, class exercises, and student projects. Topics include the process of gaining access to and participating in the social worlds of others; techniques of observation, fieldnote-taking, researcher self-monitoring and reflection; methods of inductive analysis of qualitative data including conceptual coding, grounded theory, and narrative analysis. Discussion of research ethics, the politics of fieldwork, modes of validating researcher accounts, and styles of writing up qualitative field research. 
